  array (
    'en_US' => '<p>Information for authors</p><p>1. Papers for review and possible are accepted either Spanish or English.</p><p>2. Papers can be send via e-mail word, publicaciones.economia@claustro.urosario.edu.co</p><p>or</p><p>Editor</p><p>Revista de Econom´ıa del Rosario</p><p>Facultad de Econom´ıa</p><p>Universidad del Rosario</p><p>Calle 14 No. 4 - 69</p><p>Bogot´a, Colombia.</p><p>3. Papers must be original work.</p><p>4. The first page of the paper should contain the following information:</p><p><em>• </em>Title.</p><p><em>• </em>Name and institutional affiliation.</p><p><em>• </em>Abstract no longer than 100 words in Spanish and English.</p><p><em>• </em>JEL codes and keywords.</p><p><em>• </em>Footnote with name, address, telephone, fax and e-mail of all authors.</p><p>Acknowledge and information of grants received by the authors</p><p>can be provided in this footnote, as well as thanks.</p><p>5. Papers should be written in a way such that they contain no information</p><p>regarding authorship.</p><p>6. Papers should be double spaced, wide margins and one sided printed,</p><p>and not exceed 40 pages.</p><p>7. Footnotes should be exclusively used to clarify.</p><p>8. Figures and tables should be numbered consecutively in the text in arabic</p><p>numerals.</p><p>9. Equations should be numbered consecutively throughout the document.</p><p>10. Titles and subtitles should be numbered as follows:</p><p>1. Title 1</p><p>1.1. Subtitle</p><p>1.1.1. Sub subtitle</p><p>2. Title 2</p><p>11. The reference list must include all references cited in the document, and</p><p>should be listed in the following style:</p><p>For books</p><p>Layard, R., Nickell, S., Jackman, R. (1991). Unemployment: Macroeconomic</p><p>Performance and the Labour Market . Oxford University Press:</p><p>Oxford.</p><p>For journal articles</p><p>Urbain, J. (1992). ”On weak exogeneity in error correction models”. Oxford</p><p>Bulletin of Economics and Statistics 52, 187-202.</p><p>For contributions 